-- Rangers Beat Capitals 1-0 to Force Game 7 in NHL Playoff Series
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2013-05-12T23:10:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-12/rangers-beat-capitals-1-0-to-force-game-7-in-nhl-playoff-series.html
The  New York Rangers  beat the
Washington Capitals 1-0 to force a decisive seventh game in
their National Hockey League playoff series.  Derick Brassard scored the game’s lone goal at 9:39 of the
second period at New York’s Madison Square Garden. Henrik
Lundqvist made 27 saves for the shutout.  The Capitals, the third seed in the Eastern Conference,
will host Game 7 of the best-of-seven first-round series
tomorrow.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  